changelist.name: V2 Changelist
changelist.comment: Switched to new list after starting work upon V2 of the program.

task.summary:
10/10/2016 Update #1
Completed: - Client Status combobox now correctly loads the client's based on if they're active / inactive. - Invoice table now correctly loads all of a Client's invoices. Irregardless of which project the invoice is assigned to. - Created new Invoice and InvoiceBuilder classes. - Optimized some back-end code.

10/11/2016 Update #1
Goal: - Prep the GUI & database for a presentation to the client tomorrow. - Success.
Completed: - Exported JavaFX App into a JAR file. - Filepaths are properly configured for the JAR to load all FXML files. - Connection to database is established correctly & works as expected while in a JAR.

10/12/2016 Update #1
Completed: - Added a lot of the FXML documents to resources. - Changed naming convention for FXML resources.

10/12/2016 Update #2
Completed: - Re-wrote a lot of code. - Treview now shows the Clients & their projects. - Contact & Invoice table now shower the information of their respective selection. - Notes now displays the notes of its respective selection.

10/15/2016 Update #1
Completed: - Rewrote a bunch more code. - Switched to using tasks & threads in order to off-load the work from the main application thread. - Switching to this fixed the lag that was occurring in the application. - Introduced an abstract class for loading new screens. - Removed the old multi-screen loader system. - It didn't allow you to open a screen and sizeToScene(). - This caused many forms to look out of place or over-sized. - Took advantage of Java 8 and replaced most event handlers with lambda's.

10/15/2016 Update #2
Completed: - Client and Project notes now load when selected. - Notes for each type are saved depending on their type. - Updates are sent to the database & work 100%. - Customer Tab appears to be 80% functional.

10/15/2016 Update #3
Completed: - Switched from 1 main controller for all tabs to 1 controller for each tab. - Each new tab is included upon loading. - Switched package name.

10/15/2016 - Update #4
Completed: - Implemented abstract classes for loading screens & connecting to the database. - Split all controller into having their own database connections, that way nothing ever gets overloaded. - Also saves time for maintaining the code.
To-Do: - Fix the stupid bug that is causing a null pointer exception when you click an expansion arrow inside TreeView.

10/16/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Fixed the bug that was causing a null pointer exception inside of the treeview event handler.

10/16/2016 - Update #2
Completed: - New -> New Invoice now loads the New Invoice screen. - New Invoice screen loads all information it needs from the database. - Transitioned some methods to new threads to spread some of the work. - Fixed all SQL statements to include a "Order by ASC". Everything now loads alphabetically.

10/16/2016 - Update #3
Completed: - Implemented the Save and Cancel buttons.

10/16/2016 - Update #4
Completed: - Transitioned everything that could be over to package-private.

10/18/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Fixed an error with the Contact class. Was causing the JAR'd version to throw hella errors.

10/18/2016 - Update #2
Completed: - Fixed an error in the NewInvoice Screen. - The "Cancel" button did not exit correctly. - Added the New Project screen. Basic functionality is working, but does not update the database currently.

10/18/2016 - Update #3
Completed: - Added New > Invoice - Basic functionality is established. - Added New > Contact - Loads a small pop-up that asks which type of contact you would like to create. - Full functionality established for this screen. - Added New > Contact > Customer - Added New > Contact > Project - Added New > Contact > Supplier - Added New > Contact > Vendor - Basic functionality established for all 4 screens.

10/18/2016 - Update #4
Completed: - Added New > Customer - Basic functionality is established. - Country and State lists load correctly.
I think the Customer tab is 90% complete?

10/18/2016 - Update #5
Completed: - Began work on Employee Tab. - The employee status loads correctly, and reloads when an action is performed upon it. - The employee TreeView loads employee's by their type for easier management. - Fixed a major issue with how the TreeView was loading children. - The math in the for loops was incorrect and was skipping over Parents and giving children to the wrong parent. - Adjusted how the math was being calculated and the issue was resolved. - This issue occurred for both the Customers tab and the Employee tab.
- Merging.

10/31/16 - Update #1
Completed: - Completed transition from strings to objects for country and region in the New & Edit Client controllers.

10/31/16 - Update #3
Completed: - New Employee and Edit Employee Works. - New Invoice Works.
Broke: - I broke the EmployeeTreeView. Idk how... sorry mom!

11/1/16 - Update #1
Completed: - Fixed the broken EmployeeTreeView. - Had forgotten to set the employee's fullName value, and so it was blank. - Fixed another issue with loading the new Employee screen. - Had forgotten to establish a connection with the database.

11/1/16 - Update #2
Completed: - Added status and type menu's to all contact screens.

11/1/16 - Update #3
Completed: - Can now create Change orders. - If no company or project is selected, a pop-up appears asking for that information. - If a company is selected, a pop-up appears asking for project information. - If a project is selected, the new change order form appears.

11/1/16 - Update #4
Completed: - A bug was causing issues where if the edit button was clicked without anything being selected, it would throw a null pointer exception. This has been fixed.

11/1/16 - Update #5
Completed: - Completed half of the change order form.

11/2/16 - Update #1
Completed: - Change order form fully implemented.

11/2/16 - Update #2
Completed: - New Employee Project Assignment fully implemented. - New Employee Vehicle Assignment fully implemented.

11/2/16 - Update #4
Completed: - New Employee form is complete. - Edit Employee is fully implemented.

11/2/16 - Minor Update #1
Completed: - Performed Code Analysis.

11/4/16 - Update #1
Completed: - Employee's assigned projects now load up when you select the respective employee.

11/6/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Vehicles have been changed to hold a make and model object, rather than string. - This makes it easier to retrieve information later, rather than hitting the database again. - Vehicles Tab is now 50% complete. - Need to implement the button functions and database updates.

11/6/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Vehicles have been changed to hold a make and model object, rather than string. - This makes it easier to retrieve information later, rather than hitting the database again. - Vehicles Tab is now 50% complete. - Need to implement the button functions and database updates.

11/6/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Vehicles have been changed to hold a make and model object, rather than string. - This makes it easier to retrieve information later, rather than hitting the database again. - Vehicles Tab is now 50% complete. - Need to implement the button functions and database updates.

11/6/2016 - Update #2
Completed: - Updated new & edit forms for client and employee. - Changed some field sizes & removed client type.

11/6/2016 - Update #3
Completed: - Added some more features to the VehicleTab. - Started working on how to display reports.

11/7/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Small change to the way that vehicle year's are generated.

11/7/2016 - Update #2
Completed: - Finishing touches on the vehicle tab.

11/8/2016 - Update #1
Completed: - Finished the back-end for the report viewer window. - Provide a query to the db connection and it will pop up with the correct columns and rows in a table view. - 100% tests so far.

11/8/2016 - Update #2
Completed: - Customer screen now loads the appropriate edit screen depending on what has been selected. - Options are Client, Project, Client Contact, Project Contact and Invoice.

11/8/2016 - Update #3
Completed: - Employee screen now loads the appropriate edit screen depending on what has been selected. - Options are Employee, Employee Assigned Project, and Employee Assigned Vehicle.

11/11/16
Pushing to work from another computer.

Completed: - Editing any type of contact now works 100%.

11/13/16 - Update #2
Completed: - Implemented employee history log. - Wrapping up the program, it doesn't need to all be done for turning in.

11/16/16 - Update #1
Completed: - Finished Report Tab.

11/16/16 - Update #2
Completed: - Updated Employee Tab.

Completed: - Finished Employee and Customer Tabs.

11/17/16 - Update #2
Completed: - Finished Edit Invoice.

Completed: - Started implementing new job data sheet form.
